<section id="introduction">
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to our evening walking tour in Ulaanbaatar! This tour is designed for those who are passionate about history, especially the Soviet era. Join us for a 2-hour exploration of Ulaanbaatar's historical and cultural sites from the 20th century.</p>
</section>

<section id="destinations">
    <h2>Destinations and Historical Aspects of Ulaanbaatar</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Gandantegchinlen Monastery</li>
        <li>Sukhbaatar Square</li>
        <li>State Department Store</li>
        <li>National Academic Theatre of Opera and Ballet of Mongolia</li>
        <li>The Beatles Monument</li>
        <li>Various Soviet-era architecture and landmarks</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section id="agenda">
    <h2>Agenda of the Walk</h2>
    <p>Our tour will cover the following points of interest:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Introduction and brief history of Ulaanbaatar</li>
        <li>Visit to Gandantegchinlen Monastery</li>
        <li>Walk through Sukhbaatar Square</li>
        <li>Explore the State Department Store and its significance</li>
        <li>Visit to the National Academic Theatre of Opera and Ballet of Mongolia</li>
        <li>End the tour at The Beatles Monument</li>
    </ol>
</section>

<section id="schedule">
    <h2>Schedule</h2>
    <p>The tour operates every evening from 6 PM to 8 PM. Please arrive at least 10 minutes early for registration.</p>
</section>

<section id="route">
    <h2>Walking Route</h2>
    <p>The walking route covers approximately 3 kilometers, starting from Gandantegchinlen Monastery and ending at The Beatles Monument. The route is designed to give you a comprehensive view of Ulaanbaatar's historical and cultural landscape.</p>
</section>

